amalir. Those calling themselves Free Cities Elves can also include Elves whose bloodline has mingled with that of Humans."],"page":63,"settings":[{"name":"fantasy","source":"crb"},{"name":"Terrinoth"}]},{"name":"Half-Catfolk","characteristics":{"brawn":2,"agility":2,"intellect":2,"cunning":2,"willpower":2,"presence":2},"wt":10,"st":9,"xp":100,"skills":{"skills":["cool"],"ranksTotal":1,"ranksEach":1,"description":["Half-Catfolk begin with one rank in {@skill Cool||crb}. You still cannot train their {@skill Cool||crb} above rank 2 during character creation."],"choice":false},"abilities":[{"name":"Catfolk Ancestry","description":["Half-Catfolk choose either the Claws or Fleet of Paw special ability from the {@archetype Catfolk} entry."]}],"description":["Though village-dwelling Catfolk predominantly keep to themselves, those exiled into the world must find their place among the other races. This often leads to love, marriage, and offspring.","Half-Catfolk most often retain the reflexes, senses, and coordination of their Catfolk parent, but commonly gain the aesthetics of their other parent's species. Many Half-Catfolk appear as heavily furred Humans with cat-like ears and clawed fingers, though there are nearly limitless variations. While most of the nearby societies accept such beings for what they are, full-blooded Catfolk see them as the byproducts of unworthy exiles. Thus, Half-Catfolk are often shunned and ridiculed by their pure-blooded cousins."],"page":68,"settings":[{"name":"fantasy","source":"crb"},{"name":"Terrinoth"}]},{"name":"Highborn Elf","nickname":"Elf (Highborn)","characteristics":{"brawn":2,"agility":3,"intellect":2,"cunning":2,"willpower":1,"presence":2},"wt":9,"st":10,"xp":90,"skills":{"skills":["negotiation"],"ranksTotal":1,"ranksEach":1,"description":["Highborn Elves begin with one rank in {@skill Negotiation||crb}. You still cannot train their {@skill Negotiation||crb} above rank 2 during character creation."],"choice":false},"abilities":[{"nam